    "english_translation": "Narrated by Fadala ibn Ubaid: The Messenger of Allah ﷺ was brought on the day of Khaibar a necklace with beads suspended in gold. A man purchased it for seven dinars. He came to the Prophet ﷺ and mentioned that to him. The Prophet ﷺ said: 'No, until you distinguish between them.' He said: 'I only intended the beads.' The Prophet ﷺ said: 'No, until you distinguish between them.' So he returned it until he had separated them.",
